body.section:
Creating documents
Create the document mnunberg.json. It can be anywhere on your file system:{ "name": "Mark Nunberg", "email": "mark.nunberg@couchbase.com", "privs": ["admin"], "location": { "country": "United States", "state": "NV", "city": "Reno" }, "following": [ "u:tgreenstein", "u:ingenthr", "u:potus" ], "likes": ["doge", "pastries"] }
Now, insert the document into Couchbase using the cbc utility:$ cbc create --mode insert mnunberg < mnunberg.jsonmnunberg is the document’s ID. The command pipes the document's content to the cbc command’s standard input.
